import React, { useEffect } from "react"; import { Link } from "react-router-dom"; import Pagenav from "../Nav/Pagenav"; import "./About.scss"; import { gsap } from "gsap"; import file from "../../Resume/ArnavResume.pdf"; const navData = [{ work: "Home" }]; const About = () => { const doAnimate = () => { const tl = gsap.timeline(); tl.to(".about-overlay", { bottom: "100%", duration: 1, ease: "expo.in", }).to(".header", { y: 0, duration: 1, ease: "expo.inOut", }); }; useEffect(() => { doAnimate(); }, []); return (

About

I'm Arnav, a Java Backend Developer and DSA enthusiast.


I contributed the migration of the legacy OmniDocs Enterprise Content Management system from a Java EJB architecture to a modern Spring Boot microservices framework, leveraging my expertise in the field. I optimized database procedures across PostgreSQL, MSSQL, and Oracle SQL to ensure smooth integration with the new microservices architecture while adhering to best practices. Additionally, I developed and automated integration test cases using JUnit to enhance interaction accuracy between software components. I also managed and addressed various vulnerability scan reports, including Checkmarx, Ready API, and SCA Dependency Analysis, throughout all stages of the project lifecycle to maintain continuous security compliance.


Since my college years, I have been actively honing my algorithmic problem-solving skills on platforms such as LeetCode, HackerRank, and Codeforces. With a deep understanding of data structures and algorithms, I have tackled a substantial number of challenges. Notably, I rank in the top 7% on LeetCode with a rating of 1789.


In Frontend I have worked on React (the Javascript library), having knowledge of hooks, Context, state management using Redux, as well as practising advanced animations using GSAP. I am also versed in HTML, CSS and SASS (advanced CSS).


Sometimes it is the people who no one imagines anything of who do the things that no one can imagine.

In the backend, I have worked on Spring Boot for developing REST APIs. I have also worked on a stand-alone Spring MVC project in my internship in which the frontend part of the application was managed with Thymeleaf following the proper MVC model with the creation of Controller, Services and DAO layers.


I also often write discussion articles related to problem solving on Leetcode and post small projects related to development on Codepen.
